                                                                                                                                Buttons

                                                                                                                                Timed button

                                                                                                                                Stable

                                                                                                                                Timed buttons are used as a variation of our rectangle buttons. The main difference is that, unlike standard ones, timed buttons auto-advance the user after a finite amount of time (usually a few seconds).

                                                                                                                                Usage
                                                                                                                                Specs
                                                                                                                                Status & changelog
                                                                                                                                Common alternative names
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Timer button, countdown button, offer button, auto-advance timer


                                                                                                                                Questions, comments, feedback?

                                                                                                                                Leave a comment in Figma or reach out to us on Slack.

                                                                                                                                #base-design-support


                                                                                                                                Anatomy

                                                                                                                                The timed button closely follows the anatomy of a standard Base rectangle button. The two main differences are that the timed button includes a second label for the timer and an overlay to indicate timer progress. All of the elements below are required. An optional leading and trailing icon can be added as well.

                                                                                                                                Leading
                                                                                                                                Trailing
                                                                                                                                Leading and trailing

                                                                                                                                Hierarchy

                                                                                                                                Usage

                                                                                                                                Timed buttons should be used sparingly to notify users that the current screen that they are on requires their immediate and timely attention

                                                                                                                                Optional actions

                                                                                                                                If misused, timed buttons can cause more harm than good. Ensure usage of these buttons is tied only to optional flows and actions and not interacting with them will cause no degradation in the overall quality of our products, services, or experiences.

                                                                                                                                Use cases

                                                                                                                                Timed offers
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Help users make a decision between two products, tradeoff between speed and cost, etc.

                                                                                                                                Focus on tasks at hand
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Increase user productivity by enabling quick auto-confirmation on actions that are extremely familiar, have a low learning curve and a low decline/dropoff rate.

                                                                                                                                Use timeout to limit actions
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Timed buttons can be used to limit the number of times a user can take a certain action.

                                                                                                                                Create a buffer to reverse action
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Allow users, who realize they made a mistake or change their mind, to cancel an action within a certain amount of time after it has been triggered.

                                                                                                                                Continuous transparency

                                                                                                                                Use the provided numerical countdown to reinforce how much time a user has left to take action and ensure all users can comprehend it (incl. screen readers).

                                                                                                                                This is especially important for accessibility

                                                                                                                                Users with cognitive disabilities find it even harder to decide when time limits are unclear. Users with visual impairments cannot see the visual affordance, so the remaining explicit time makes this button accessible to them with a screen reader.

                                                                                                                                Don’t
                                                                                                                                Solely using visual indicators to communicate time sensitivity will be challenging for users with some cognitive disabilities, as well as users with vision impairements
                                                                                                                                Don’t
                                                                                                                                Two line layous are strictly reserved for localization & dynamic type and should not be used otherwise.

                                                                                                                                Asking for more time

                                                                                                                                We highly encourage thinking about ways to enable users to set their preferences when it comes to time – whether that's asking for extended timers or disabling them completely.

                                                                                                                                There are a few ways a user should ask for more time:

                                                                                                                                Explicit action

                                                                                                                                One way to allow for more time is to present a visible trigger to extend the remaining time.

                                                                                                                                Talk to your engineers before implementing this pattern – although easy in Figma, it might be challenging to implement on products where the time is being sent from the backend.

                                                                                                                                Setting preferences

                                                                                                                                Users should be able to set a preference on a product or system level to define their needs when it comes to time.

                                                                                                                                FTUX
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Consider using a regular button the first time you introduce a new experience (that a user will continue to see frequently) and give them the option to save their preference for next time.

                                                                                                                                Returning user
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                During their next session, you can switch out the preferred choice to the saved preference and use a timed button to auto-advance them.

                                                                                                                                Don't forget to create a place for them to change their preference!

                                                                                                                                Behavior

                                                                                                                                States

                                                                                                                                Preloading
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Preloading states indicate an interim state when the content within the element is being loaded. The loading state for most image and text content uses a placeholder component.

                                                                                                                                Enabled
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                A timed button is counting down right away in the enabled state before a user interacts with it.

                                                                                                                                Pressed / Mousedown
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Text and icons: contentInversePrimary

                                                                                                                                Container: backgroundInversePrimary + 20% white overlay

                                                                                                                                Focus
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Text and icons: contentInversePrimary

                                                                                                                                Container: backgroundInversePrimary

                                                                                                                                Outline: 3px borderAccent

                                                                                                                                Disabled
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Text and icons: contentStateDisabled

                                                                                                                                Container: backgroundStateDisabled

                                                                                                                                Loading
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Container: backgroundInversePrimary

                                                                                                                                Spinner matches icon size for Large Button

                                                                                                                                Moving forward/backward in the flow



                                                                                                                                Proactive versus timeout interaction

                                                                                                                                Users can tap or click a timed button or do nothing as the timer completes. Both result in the timed button's action being executed

                                                                                                                                Proactive

                                                                                                                                If a user wants to proactively choose the auto-advance action before the timer is up, let them. This helps them feel in control and doesn’t stop them from moving forward in the flow.

                                                                                                                                Timeout

                                                                                                                                Once the timer has reached 0, the action bound to the timed button will be taken on behalf of the user.

                                                                                                                                Motion and timing

                                                                                                                                When using timed buttons, ensure that the larger UI presentation layer they are part of is on the screen long enough for all users to decide and acknowledge the change.

                                                                                                                                Timing is crucial for users with disabilities, where having a shorter timer can contribute to a negative experience.

                                                                                                                                Use case

                                                                                                                                People with physical disabilities often need more time to react, interact with screens, and complete activities.

                                                                                                                                People with low vision need more time to locate things on the screen and to read them.

                                                                                                                                People who are blind and using a screen reader may often need more time to have things read out loud, orient themselves, understand screen layouts, find information, and operate controls.

                                                                                                                                And then people who are deaf and communicate in sign language may need more time to read the information when it's printed in text because their first language might be sign language.

                                                                                                                                People who have cognitive or language limitations need more time to read and to understand and process.

                                                                                                                                Do
                                                                                                                                Keep the button and its container for at least 15-20sec to ensure users have enough time to read and process.
                                                                                                                                Caution
                                                                                                                                Do not use a timer of under 10sec - this is way too short and will most likely cause a spike in errors and unhappy users.


                                                                                                                                Timing presets

                                                                                                                                Preset

                                                                                                                                Time

                                                                                                                                Note

                                                                                                                                Short

                                                                                                                                30 sec

                                                                                                                                Give the user 30 seconds to read your content and make an informed decision.

                                                                                                                                Medium

                                                                                                                                45 sec

                                                                                                                                Give the user 45 seconds to read your content and make an informed decision.

                                                                                                                                Long

                                                                                                                                75 sec

                                                                                                                                Give the user 75 seconds to read your content and make an informed decision.

                                                                                                                                Custom

                                                                                                                                8 sec <= custom

                                                                                                                                You can set a custom duration of the timer, with an absolute minimum of 15 seconds, to ensure most users can make an informed decision and read through the content.

                                                                                                                                Breakpoints

                                                                                                                                Sliding buttons should follow the same Button breakpoints rules defined in our documentation.
